      "content": "it just feels like there isn't any real \"way out\" with money. the numbers dont lie. when i look at the bank account and then look at the kids and see what they're missing out on because of my failures, it just feels so logical that the math doesnt add up. like, if i wasn't here, they could at least use the insurance or whatever and actually have a chance at a decent life without me constantly failing them. it's just a math problem at this point.",
